<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="249" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,258,1003]" pageId="4" pageNumber="249">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,418,330,355]" pageId="4" pageNumber="249">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,410,331,355]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="249">Derivatio nominis</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
The name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Trivinho-Strixino &amp; Shimabukuro" authorityYear="2018" box="[555,667,332,355]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Pseudochironomus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="249" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ariquemis">
<emphasis box="[555,667,332,355]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="249">ariquemis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
refers to the locality where the species was collected, Ariquemis River. The name is treated as a noun in apposition.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,258,1003]" pageId="4" pageNumber="249">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,457,402,427]" pageId="4" pageNumber="249">Diagnostic characters</emphasis>
. Adult male of 
<taxonomicName authority="Trivinho-Strixino &amp; Shimabukuro, 2018" authorityName="Trivinho-Strixino &amp; Shimabukuro" authorityYear="2018" box="[634,966,402,427]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Pseudochironomus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="249" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ariquemis" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[634,966,402,427]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="249">Pseudochironomus ariquemis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[973,1037,402,427]" pageId="4" pageNumber="249">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[973,1037,402,427]" pageId="4" pageNumber="249" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
differs from all other species of the genus by the combination of the following characters. Adult male: thorax with acrosticals; anal point absent in hypopygium; superior volsella hook-shaped, with three simple setae; median volsella short with two setae; pars ventralis completely divided; inferior volsella with microtrichia and several marginal large setae; transverse sternapodeme without oral projections. Pupa: sternite I with two short anterior pair of fine spines; comb of segment VIII with one large tooth and 4–6 marginal teeth. Larva: AR = 1.42; mentum 169 µm long, with eleven brown teeth; median tooth longer than laterals.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="250" pageId="4" pageNumber="249" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,258,1003]" box="[199,1208,654,679]" pageId="4" pageNumber="249">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,412,654,679]" pageId="4" pageNumber="249">Description. Male</emphasis>
(n = 1). Head, wings and legs not discernible inside the pupal exuviae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,258,1003]" box="[199,597,690,715]" pageId="4" pageNumber="249">
<emphasis box="[199,280,690,715]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="249">Thorax</emphasis>
. Ac 7; Dc 14; Pa 3; Scts 17.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,258,1003]" pageId="4" pageNumber="249">
<emphasis box="[199,342,727,750]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="249">Hypopygium</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[368,500,726,751]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1694,1716]" captionTargetBox="[362,1229,1049,1629]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[340,1247,1037,1673]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Pseudochironomus ariquemis sp. n. male. (a) Hypopygium. (b) Hypopygium, right ventral view,left dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1212171/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="249">Fig. 3a, b</figureCitation>
). Tergite IX without anal point. Laterosternite with four setae. Transverse sternapodeme 70 µm long, without oral projections. Phallapodeme 169 µm long. Pars ventralis narrow, 45 µm long. Gonocoxite 123 µm long. Superior volsella hooklike, with three preapical simple setae. Median volsella rounded with two simple setae. Inferior volsella pubescent with 10 ventro-marginal large setae. Gonostylus 146 µm long. HR 0.84.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,258,1003]" pageId="4" pageNumber="249">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,261,906,931]" pageId="4" pageNumber="249">Pupa</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[282,357,906,931]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1452,1474]" captionTargetBox="[526,1004,469,1413]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[513,1073,447,1430]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Pseudochironomus ariquemis sp. n. pupa. (a) Sternite I. (b, c) Abdominal tergite. (d) Posterolateral spurs of segment VIII." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1212173/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="249">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis box="[382,536,906,931]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="249">Cephalotorax</emphasis>
. Frontal apotome strongly granulose. Cephalic tubercles short; frontal setae absent. Thorax strongly granulose; two antepronotals, longest setae 181 µm long; three precorneals and four dorsocentrals. Distance Dc1-Dc2 75 µm; Dc2-Dc3 390 µm; Dc3-Dc4 31 µm.
</paragraph>
<caption box="[151,1430,1694,1716]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1212171/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="249" startId="4.[151,250,1694,1716]" targetBox="[362,1229,1049,1629]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1430,1694,1716]" box="[151,1430,1694,1716]" pageId="4" pageNumber="249">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,269,1694,1716]" pageId="4" pageNumber="249">FIGURE 3</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Trivinho-Strixino &amp; Shimabukuro, 2018" authorityName="Trivinho-Strixino &amp; Shimabukuro" authorityYear="2018" box="[281,581,1695,1716]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Pseudochironomus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="249" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ariquemis" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[281,581,1695,1716]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="249">Pseudochironomus ariquemis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[588,645,1695,1716]" pageId="4" pageNumber="249">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[588,645,1695,1716]" pageId="4" pageNumber="249" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
male. (a) Hypopygium. (b) Hypopygium, right ventral view, left dorsal view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1756,2033]" pageId="4" pageNumber="249">
<emphasis box="[199,305,1756,1781]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="249">Abdomen</emphasis>
. Length 
<quantity box="[404,493,1757,1781]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.7" pageId="4" pageNumber="249" unit="mm" value="3.7">3.7 mm</quantity>
. Sternite I with two anterior pair of fine spines (
<figureCitation box="[1028,1110,1756,1781]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1452,1474]" captionTargetBox="[526,1004,469,1413]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[513,1073,447,1430]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Pseudochironomus ariquemis sp. n. pupa. (a) Sternite I. (b, c) Abdominal tergite. (d) Posterolateral spurs of segment VIII." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1212173/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="249">Fig. 4a</figureCitation>
). Tergite I bare. Tergite II-VI with variable patterns of shagreen usually forming an anterior band of stronger spines (
<figureCitation box="[1137,1222,1792,1817]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1452,1474]" captionTargetBox="[526,1004,469,1413]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[513,1073,447,1430]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Pseudochironomus ariquemis sp. n. pupa. (a) Sternite I. (b, c) Abdominal tergite. (d) Posterolateral spurs of segment VIII." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1212173/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="249">Fig. 4b</figureCitation>
). Tergite IV with a median-anterior band 194 µm long of fine spines. Tergite VII and VIII with weaker shagreenation (
<figureCitation box="[1336,1423,1828,1853]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1452,1474]" captionTargetBox="[526,1004,469,1413]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[513,1073,447,1430]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Pseudochironomus ariquemis sp. n. pupa. (a) Sternite I. (b, c) Abdominal tergite. (d) Posterolateral spurs of segment VIII." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1212173/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="249">Fig. 4c</figureCitation>
). Hooklets row extending nearly on 1/3 the width of tergite II. Pedes spurii B short on segment II. Pedes spurii A present in segment IV. Conjunctives III/IV to IV/V with continuous bands of spinules. Tergite VIII with posterolateral comb, with one large tooth and 4–6 marginal teeth (
<figureCitation box="[901,986,1936,1961]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1452,1474]" captionTargetBox="[526,1004,469,1413]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[513,1073,447,1430]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Pseudochironomus ariquemis sp. n. pupa. (a) Sternite I. (b, c) Abdominal tergite. (d) Posterolateral spurs of segment VIII." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1212173/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="249">Fig. 4d</figureCitation>
). Segments I-IV with 0, 3, 3, 3 L setae, respectively; segments V-VI with three taeniae; segments VII- VIII with four taeniae. Anal lobe 310 µm long, with anterior weak shagreenation and complete fringe of taeniae. Genital sac 440 µm long.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,395]" pageId="5" pageNumber="250">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,491,151,176]" pageId="5" pageNumber="250">4th instar larva exuviae</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[510,582,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1860,1882]" captionTargetBox="[232,1371,620,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[208,1375,594,1801]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 5. Pseudochironomus ariquemis sp. n. larva.(a) Antenna. (b) Dorsal sclerites of head.(c) Labral lamella and SI. (d) Premandible.(e) Mandible.(f) Mentum and ventromental plate." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1212175/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="250">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). Antenna (
<figureCitation box="[721,804,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1860,1882]" captionTargetBox="[232,1371,620,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[208,1375,594,1801]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 5. Pseudochironomus ariquemis sp. n. larva.(a) Antenna. (b) Dorsal sclerites of head.(c) Labral lamella and SI. (d) Premandible.(e) Mandible.(f) Mentum and ventromental plate." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1212175/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="250">Fig. 5a</figureCitation>
) 126 µm, basal segment 74 µm long, AR 1.42. Large Lauterborn organs on apex of 2nd segment. Blade 64 µm, surpassing 5th segment. Dorsal sclerites of head as in figure 5b. Pecten epipharyngis composed by 3 plates. Labral lamella and SI as in figure 5c. Premandible (
<figureCitation box="[1346,1427,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1860,1882]" captionTargetBox="[232,1371,620,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[208,1375,594,1801]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 5. Pseudochironomus ariquemis sp. n. larva.(a) Antenna. (b) Dorsal sclerites of head.(c) Labral lamella and SI. (d) Premandible.(e) Mandible.(f) Mentum and ventromental plate." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1212175/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="250">Fig. 5d</figureCitation>
) 120 µm long with two large teeth; brush present. Mandible (
<figureCitation box="[851,933,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1860,1882]" captionTargetBox="[232,1371,620,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[208,1375,594,1801]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 5. Pseudochironomus ariquemis sp. n. larva.(a) Antenna. (b) Dorsal sclerites of head.(c) Labral lamella and SI. (d) Premandible.(e) Mandible.(f) Mentum and ventromental plate." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1212175/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="250">Fig. 5e</figureCitation>
) 208 µm long, with one strong clear apical tooth and four brown inner teeth. Seta subdentalis slender, 58 µm long, not surpasses apical tooth. Mentum (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1860,1882]" captionTargetBox="[232,1371,620,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[208,1375,594,1801]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 5. Pseudochironomus ariquemis sp. n. larva.(a) Antenna. (b) Dorsal sclerites of head.(c) Labral lamella and SI. (d) Premandible.(e) Mandible.(f) Mentum and ventromental plate." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1212175/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="250">Fig. 5f</figureCitation>
) 169 µm wide with eleven brown teeth; median tooth longer than first laterals; 2nd laterals recessive and fused to first laterals. Ventramental plates 125 µm long, with very distinct striations and touching at the midline.
</paragraph>
